<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>History of the Stock Market</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f2f5fa;
            padding: 20px;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }
        h1 {
            text-align: center;
            color: #1a237e;
        }
        .container {
            max-width: 900px;
            margin: auto;
            background: white;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 10px;
        }
        .section {
            margin-bottom: 30px;
        }
        img {
            width: 100%;
            height: 350px;
            object-fit: cover;
            border-radius: 8px;
            margin-top: 10px;
        }
        p {
            font-size: 16px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>History of the Stock Market</h1>

<div class="container">

    <div class="section">
        <p>
            The history of the stock market began when people started trading ownership in businesses.
            In ancient times, traders invested money in public projects and trade activities.
        </p>
        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1605106715994-18d3fecffb98" alt="Ancient trade illustration">
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <p>
            During the Middle Ages, merchants pooled money together to fund long trade journeys,
            sharing both profits and losses.
        </p>
        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1545156521-77bd85671d30" alt="Medieval trade market">
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <p>
            In 1602, the first official stock exchange was established in Amsterdam,
            allowing people to buy and sell company shares.
        </p>
        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1589829545856-d10d557cf95f" alt="Early stock exchange">
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <p>
            Stock trading later expanded to Britain, leading to the establishment
            of the London Stock Exchange in 1801.
        </p>
        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1513635269975-59663e0ac1ad" alt="London financial district">
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <p>
            In the United States, trading began on Wall Street and eventually led
            to the formation of the New York Stock Exchange.
        </p>
        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1542224566-6e85f2e6772f" alt="Wall Street New York">
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <p>
            Today, stock markets operate digitally using computers and the internet,
            playing a major role in the global economy.
        </p>
        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1535320404287-416eae6b57a9" alt="Modern stock market screens">
    </div>

</div>

</body>
</html>
